**A REALM IS ENTERED... AGAIN**

Welcome to the Realm.

>> _Haven't I heard this already?_

Let's tell you a bit about why you are here.

The Realm is a massive world, a world in some sense placed on top of the world that you currently inhabit. The Realm is a More Convenient World. What we mean is that the Realm allows you to do things that you would be unable to do in real life, simply because it is a game. Instead of taking an airline trip and wasting hours of time, you can simply teleport to designated teleportation spots located all around the world. Instead of wasting thousands on decor, you can buy furniture for nominal prices#footnote 21#. Ever wanted to play a Stradivarius? Ever wanted to own a grand piano? 

((bluh))

#21 VeraGames claims that the reason you have to pay for a bed/couch/whatever at all is that it needs to dedicate some fraction of a CPU to physics simulation. Any CS major with half a brain can tell you this is total hogwash. With today's hyptherthreaded polycores, the cost of simulating a couch is equal to an insultingly small number of penny atoms. ((maybe trying tooo hard))

>> _Neat._

VeraGames concurs! 

But the Realm would not be a true game without an end goal. A mission to accomplish.

VeraGames attempts to create the perfect Scenario for each Player. We will integrate you in the Realm by allowing you to do what you would be the most interesting in. For instance, we provide artists with the best set of tools available; writers with organization and quiet, and so on#footnote 16#.

_Dan tries to think of what this might be._

_Although Dan works an 8-5 programming job, if pressed he would probably admit that the most interesting work he's ever done was several years ago, when he played hacker. He finds tearing things down to be more interesting intellectually, somehow. There is an appeal, he would argue, to the match of wits._

_Programming was always a fight against the self._

_But hacking. Hacking was you against another. You had to figure out his mistakes, his the cracks in the mortar, while not making any yourself._

_But certainly the most compelling part, for Dan, was the aspect of doing something_ he was not supposed to do. _He wonders how the realm could ever mimick that._

>> _You weren't quite so helpful last time._

VeraGames is always learning. 

